sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Notebook as Jupyter Notebook<br/>8080/TCP HTTPS
    participant TrainOp as Training Operator
    participant TrainJob as PyTorchJob Pod<br/>Distributed Training
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant ModelReg as Model Registry<br/>8080/TCP HTTPS
    participant KServe as KServe Controller
    participant Istio as Istio Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Predictor as InferenceService Pod<br/>8080/TCP mTLS
    participant TrustyAI as TrustyAI Service<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant PostgreSQL as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP TLS(optional)

    Note over User,PostgreSQL: Workflow 1: Model Training to Deployment

    User->>Dashboard: Login via OpenShift OAuth<br/>Bearer Token (JWT)
    Dashboard-->>User: Dashboard UI

    User->>Dashboard: Create Notebook CR<br/>Bearer Token
    Dashboard->>Notebook: Deploy Jupyter instance
    Notebook-->>User: Notebook URL (Route)

    User->>Notebook: Develop model code<br/>Bearer Token
    Note over User,Notebook: Interactive development

    User->>Notebook: Submit distributed training job
    Notebook->>TrainOp: Create PyTorchJob CR<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    TrainOp->>TrainJob: Deploy training pods<br/>Gang scheduling

    TrainJob->>S3: Load training data<br/>AWS IAM / S3 SigV4
    S3-->>TrainJob: Training dataset

    Note over TrainJob: Distributed training<br/>across workers

    TrainJob->>S3: Save model checkpoint<br/>AWS IAM / S3 SigV4
    S3-->>TrainJob: Checkpoint saved

    TrainJob-->>User: Training complete

    User->>Dashboard: Register model in registry
    Dashboard->>ModelReg: POST /api/model_registry/v1alpha3/models<br/>Bearer Token
    ModelReg->>PostgreSQL: Store model metadata<br/>TLS (optional)
    PostgreSQL-->>ModelReg: Metadata persisted
    ModelReg-->>Dashboard: Model registered

    User->>Dashboard: Create InferenceService
    Dashboard->>KServe: Create InferenceService CR<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    KServe->>Istio: Configure VirtualService<br/>Traffic routing
    KServe->>Predictor: Deploy predictor pod<br/>Model URI from S3

    Predictor->>S3: Download model artifacts<br/>AWS IAM / S3 SigV4
    S3-->>Predictor: Model loaded

    Predictor-->>KServe: Ready for inference
    KServe-->>Dashboard: InferenceService running

    Note over User,PostgreSQL: Inference Request Flow

    User->>Istio: POST /v2/models/model:infer<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>Bearer Token (optional)
    Istio->>Predictor: Forward request<br/>mTLS STRICT<br/>Service Identity
    Predictor-->>Istio: Prediction result<br/>JSON response
    Istio-->>User: HTTP 200 OK

    Note over TrustyAI,PostgreSQL: Monitoring Flow (async)

    Predictor->>TrustyAI: Inference payload (CloudEvents)<br/>mTLS
    TrustyAI->>PostgreSQL: Store inference data<br/>Metrics, explainability
    PostgreSQL-->>TrustyAI: Data persisted

    Note over User,TrustyAI: Model Monitoring

    User->>TrustyAI: Query model metrics<br/>Bearer Token
    TrustyAI->>PostgreSQL: Retrieve monitoring data
    PostgreSQL-->>TrustyAI: Metrics data
    TrustyAI-->>User: Fairness, drift, explainability metrics
